Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, with low specific gravity and abnormal urine appearance, indicating possible renal tubular dysfunction or diabetic ketoacidosis, though HbA1c is low. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Further nephrological and metabolic evaluation is recommended.
